<div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
        <h1>The AI Plug Library</h1>
        <p>This is your central command center for mastering automation. You have access to three powerful resources. Here's how to use them to go from zero to a confident automation builder who can solve real business problems.</p>
        
        <div class="hub-section">
            <h2>1. Start Here: The Courses</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To build a deep, foundational understanding of AI and automation from the ground up.</p>
            <p>Each course is designed to equip you with a specific, high-value skill set:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>The Prompt Course:</strong> Learn the art of prompt engineering. This course covers everything you need to know to get the most out of large language models like ChatGPT.</li>
                <li><strong>The AI Creator Course:</strong> Discover how to use AI to create content, from text and images to video and audio. This course is for anyone who wants to leverage AI in their creative process.</li>
                <li><strong>The N8N Automation Course:</strong> Master the fundamentals of automation with n8n. This course will take you from the basics to building complex, real-world workflows.</li>
                <li><strong>The Vibe Coding Course:</strong> Get into the flow of coding with this unique course. It's not just about writing code, it's about the mindset and the process of creating with technology.</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/courses" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse All Courses</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="hub-section">
            <h2>2. Test Your Knowledge: The Study Guide</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To review and reinforce your knowledge of key n8n concepts and terminology.</p>
            <p>Once you've gone through the main course, use this Jeopardy-style quiz to test your understanding. Itâ€™s a fun and effective way to ensure you've internalized the core ideas before you start building complex workflows for clients.</p>
            <a href="/study" class="btn btn-secondary">Open Study Guide</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hub-section">
            <h2>3. Build & Profit: The Workflows Library</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To access over 2,500 pre-built, production-ready automations that you can use in your own business or install for clients.</p>
            <p>This is where theory meets practice. After you've mastered the concepts in the course, this library is your arsenal. Browse by category, find a workflow that solves a specific business problem, and deploy it. This is how you will save time, create value, and make money with automation.</p>
            <a href="/workflows" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse Workflows</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hub-section">
            <h2>4. Prompt & Profit: The Prompts Library</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To access over 3,000 production-ready prompts for ChatGPT that you can use for your own business, content creation, or for clients.</p>
            <p>After you've mastered automation, this library is your arsenal for AI-powered communication. Browse by category, find a prompt that solves a specific business problem, and deploy it. This is how you save time and create value with AI.</p>
            <a href="/prompts" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse Prompts</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hub-section">
            <h2>5. Execute & Scale: The Playbooks</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To provide step-by-step guides for executing complex workflows and business strategies.</p>
            <p>These playbooks are your roadmaps to success. They combine prompts, workflows, and strategies into a cohesive plan. Use them to build powerful content engines, develop full-stack applications, and scale your operations.</p>
            <div class="resource-grid">
                <% playbooks.forEach(playbook => { %>
                    <div class="resource-card">
                        <h3><%= playbook.title %></h3>
                        <p><%= playbook.description %></p>
                        <a href="/playbooks" class="btn btn-secondary">Open Playbook</a>
                    </div>
                <% }) %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
